september 11th musical tribute events at stanford september 11th musical tribute facebook twitter email print add to calendar as the tenth anniversary of the september 11 2001 attacks approaches the peninsula choral community led by schola cantorum in partnership with the stanford office for religious life and stanford department of music will pay homage to those who lost their lives and those who gave aid in this national tragedy singers from choirs throughout the bay area will join schola cantorum in presenting a moving musical tribute performing with the choir and orchestra in mozart's requiem in d minor will be local celebrated soloists christine abraham soprano malin fritz walrod alto victor floyd tenor and jeffrey fields baritone who have generously donated their talents and services to this event the public is welcome to attend free of charge to experience the memorial singing of mozart's requiem the rev scotty mclennan dean for religious life at stanford university will offer a welcome and concluding remarks for the concert an opportunity for quiet candle lighting prayer and written reflections will be offered in the side chapel of memorial church a separate alcove area inside the church from 12 noon 3 30 pm on sunday september 11 including throughout the concert tribute when sunday september 11 2011 1 30 pm approximate duration of 1 hour s where memorial church map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students tags performance music arts sponsor department of music office for religious life contact 723 1762 religious life stanford edu admission free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 287 28715 more info last modified august 30 2011
